<p>I am trying to use bootstrap buttons(<a href="http://getbootstrap.com/javascript/#buttons" rel="nofollow">http://getbootstrap.com/javascript/#buttons</a>) for my checkboxes where users has to select one or many of the options. each check box is a boolean column. But with this code, when i click on the buttons, the check boxes doesn't get selected, neither does the state change.</p>  <pre><code>  &lt;div class="btn-group btn-group-justified" data-toggle="buttons"&gt;      &lt;%= f.label :tdm, class: "btn btn-primary" do %&gt;       &lt;%= f.check_box :tdm%&gt;       beginner     &lt;% end %&gt;       &lt;%= f.label :Domination, class: "btn btn-primary" do %&gt;       &lt;%= f.check_box :casual%&gt;       casual     &lt;% end %&gt;      &lt;%= f.label :ctf, class: "btn btn-primary" do %&gt;       &lt;%= f.check_box :ctf%&gt;       competitive     &lt;% end %&gt;      &lt;%= f.label :demolition, class: "btn btn-primary" do %&gt;       &lt;%= f.check_box :demolition%&gt;       competitive     &lt;% end %&gt;   &lt;/div&gt; </code></pre>  <p>what I'm trying to accomplish  <a href="https://jsfiddle.net/DTcHh/12565/" rel="nofollow">https://jsfiddle.net/DTcHh/12565/</a></p>